<div id="review_1122427732" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1122427732" />
    <a title="Dana Al-Basha |  دانة الباشا" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5911504-dana-al-basha"><img alt="Dana Al-Basha |  دانة الباشا" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1635258301p2/5911504.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1122427732?book_show_action=true">Dec 03, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dana Al-Basha |  دانة الباشا" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dana Al-Basha |  دانة الباشا" href="/user/show/5911504-dana-al-basha">Dana Al-Basha |  دانة الباشا</a>
      </span>

          marked it as to-read


          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9879960548982" href="/book/show/13608225">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5911504-dana-al-basha?shelf=%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A5%D8%B3%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85-islam">الإسلام-islam</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5911504-dana-al-basha?shelf=own">own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5911504-dana-al-basha?shelf=%D9%83%D8%AA%D8%A8-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%A9">كتب-عربية</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1122427732" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8765135348923342429">12 years ago, in 2002, my grandma read and reread this book, she kept telling us how much it helped her, how much it made her happy. I was so much into romance then and so dreamy and young, about 16, that the idea of such an ugly cover was unbearable. But now that I&apos;m older, wiser, and no longer care for only the cover in my books and other things, I can tell you, that this book is a gem!<br/><br/>In life, you are going to experience loss, pain, grieve, depression; you are going to question your faith, pr</span>
  <span id="freeText8765135348923342429" style="display:none">12 years ago, in 2002, my grandma read and reread this book, she kept telling us how much it helped her, how much it made her happy. I was so much into romance then and so dreamy and young, about 16, that the idea of such an ugly cover was unbearable. But now that I'm older, wiser, and no longer care for only the cover in my books and other things, I can tell you, that this book is a gem!<br /><br />In life, you are going to experience loss, pain, grieve, depression; you are going to question your faith, principles, the fairness of the world; and this book is just for you. It's kind of a secret faith builder, encouraging you to stand tall and try again, to live again, no matter what made you sad.<br /><br />As a Muslim, this book speaks to me in a deeper level, and who doesn't need that? So I'm not only reading it, I bought my family and husband each a copy, because in life, no matter where you are, no matter what you do, you need to stay strong and hold on to you faith.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8765135348923342429" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


